 East London - Following numerous complaints from the members of the public about a night spot in Vincent, East London, police accompanied officials from the Buffalo City Metro to shut the place down. East London police alleged that local residents were complaining about loud music, blocked driveways, urinating on the street and an increase in theft out of motor vehicle cases around the vicinity of the club. "SAPS Cambridge responded to a call from BCMM (buffalo city metropolitan municipality), ward 18 councillor, Mr Jason Mc Dowell, ward 4 councillor Mrs Botha and PR councillor Mrs Pollock to act on these premises," said police spokesperson, Capt "A compliance inspection was conducted in these premises by the SAPS, BCMM Law Enforcement, Fire department, Disaster management and Environmental health. "On completion of the inspection, the business was ordered to stop its operations with immediate effect due to non compliance." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  